CatDescriptText: Mrs. Louise Blackwell, 1920 Webster Avenue, Third Ward, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 26, 1957, pg. 4, with question: "Do you believe we should have a state law forbidding strikes of trolley cars, buses, and taxicabs?" answer reads: "Yes, there definitely should be some kind of law to look out for the public's interest in, and dependence on, mass transportation."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Louise Blackwell wearing plaid skirt, seated with arms folded on stoop in front of wooden door and brick wall
